<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870428-0139 </DOCNO><HL> South African Trade Surplus</HL><DD> 04/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AFRICMONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON) </IN><DATELINE> JOHANNESBURG, South Africa  </DATELINE><TEXT>    South Africa's trade surplusgrew to the equivalent of $471.9 million in March from $377.3million a year earlier, converting the rand at its currentrate, the Customs and Excise Office said.   Exports increased 21%, to $1.63 billion, while imports rose 19%, to $1.15 billion. </TEXT></DOC>